    <text id="SCC0310T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                
                <p>David Bowers filed this claim in 1871 for $428.50, claiming Union troops
                    confiscated 2 horses, 1 rifle gun, 2 saddles, 2 halters, 4 bridles, bacon, flax
                    seed, vinegar, and flour from his property near Middlebrook, Augusta Co., Va.
                    The claim was disallowed in 1874. Bowers filed an additional claim, No. 20827,
                    for $382.25; it was also disallowed. See claim No. 20827 for additional
                    information.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
